        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The Brisbane-wide median days on market for houses sits around 30 to 45 days, but that figure masks significant local variation. In Brisbane's inner east suburbs such as Morningside, Hawthorne, and Camp Hill, well-priced properties typically sell within 20 to 30 days. When you include pre-campaign preparation of 2 to 4 weeks and a standard 30 to 45 day settlement period, the full timeline from engaging an agent to receiving funds is typically 10 to 16 weeks."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does selling time in Brisbane's inner east compare to outer suburbs?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Inner east suburbs consistently clear faster than the Brisbane-wide average. Suburbs such as Morningside, Camp Hill, Hawthorne, and Bulimba regularly achieve median days on market of 20 to 30 days in a healthy market. Middle-ring and outer suburbs typically run 35 to 55 days. The difference is driven by a deeper buyer pool for inner suburbs, stronger auction clearance rates, and higher concentration of equity-rich upgrader buyers who can act quickly."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "When does a Brisbane property become stale, and what should sellers do?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
